4 Savagery To Match The Numbers Of Hobburuks That Live In Your Closet, Waiting To Pounce<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Ok first off, to play this deck you need a hideously bright and disgusting sleeves. I prefer the new Metallic Atomic Green Ultra Pro sleeves, the deck needs the insanity needed to produce such hideous Hobburuks.<br />
<br />
The Star Card in this deck is far and away Dagger Strike.  There&#39;s enough pump cards and support characters to win the skirmishes, but Dagger Strikes give the little green buggers Damage +1, AND Strength +2, allowing the hobbits to kill those annoying Uruks, Sauron Orcs, and even Nazguls!  All for ZERO twilight!  All Hobbit decks should play the weapons required for this sort of card, and there&#39;s no reason not to use it!<br />
<br />
Besides that, The Hobbits are meant to stealth to site 5, but when you hit those BIG minions, boost so your not overwhelmed(Bounder helps that too) then heal with the vast array of healing allies.  Happy Frodo heals Bounder, and Hobbit Party Guest heals the healing allies while healing himself. I said &quot;heal&quot; 5 times in one sentence.  Works pretty well, move from site 1-3, to 4, then it&#39;s judgement, it you have enough stealth cards and boosts to get through 5, go for it.  Otherwise, wait a turn, get rid of shadow cards, and hope to make it to site 5-6 next turn.  Bidding depends on the opponent, but a good overall number is 4, since Sam can remove a few of them, but make sure he doesn&#39;t die on the way to site 3.  Because, Master Samwise Is Pimp!<br />
<br />
The Uruk&#39;s are a bit simpler.  Small, Cheap, Effecient Uruks early game, Troops, Lurtz, and Orthanc for the later game.  I played Brown Lands because few people outside of Moria play archers, and a Lurtz and Orthanc is devastating, 4 wounds, and 2 scary mean Damage +1 biznatches.  Plus Pillars is useless to me, and Slopes will just bite me in the bum-bum, so it came down to process of elimination.  Spies also helps against scary direct damage decks, buying you a turn of Uruk PAIN.<br />
<br />
Overall a solid, somewhat competitve and different deck.  I could see this deck getting massivly improved with the new Hobbits geared towards fighting and the new Hobbit boost cards. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=7c6543f7af2c20d9e6dc7b4953aedc35">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21158&PHPSESSID=7c6543f7af2c20d9e6dc7b4953aedc35"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21158&PHPSESSID=7c6543f7af2c20d9e6dc7b4953aedc35" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=7c6543f7af2c20d9e6dc7b4953aedc35">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
